The Kaduna State Pilgrims Welfare Board Acting Chairperson, Hajiya Hannatu Zailani, said the board targets all the 3,945 intending pilgrims for COVID-19 vaccine this year. According to her, the vaccine is one of the criteria that must be fulfilled before an intending pilgrim will be allowed to travel for this yearâ€™s hajj based on the directives by National Hajj Commission. She spoke with Daily Trust shortly after the flag-off of the vaccination exercise of the intending pilgrims at Kaduna North Local Government Area of the state.